#: ../../config/options_metadata.rst:4
msgid ":index:`Metadata Options <configuration; metadata options>`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../config/options_metadata.rst:17
msgid "**Use standardized artist names**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../config/options_metadata.rst:19
msgid ""
"Check to only use standard Artist names, rather than Artist Credits which "
"may differ slightly across tracks and releases."
msgstr ""

#: ../../config/options_metadata.rst:23
msgid ""
"If \"Artist names\" under the \"Translate names when available\" option is "
"also checked, it will override this option if a suitable alias is found."
msgstr ""

#: ../../config/options_metadata.rst:25
msgid "**Use standardized instrument credits**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../config/options_metadata.rst:27
msgid ""
"Check to only use standard names for instruments in performer relationships. "
"Uncheck to use the instruments as credited in the relationship."
msgstr ""

#: ../../config/options_metadata.rst:29
msgid "**Use standardized vocal credits**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../config/options_metadata.rst:31
msgid ""
"Check to only use standard names for vocals in performer relationships. "
"Uncheck to use the vocals as credited in the relationship."
msgstr ""

#: ../../config/options_metadata.rst:33
msgid "**Convert Unicode punctuation characters to ASCII**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../config/options_metadata.rst:35
msgid ""
"Converts Unicode punctuation characters in MusicBrainz data to ASCII for "
"consistent use of punctuation in tags. For example, right single quotation "
"marks are converted to ASCII apostrophes ('), and horizontal ellipses are "
"converted to three full stops (...)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../config/options_metadata.rst:37
msgid "**Use release relationships**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../config/options_metadata.rst:39
msgid ""
"Check to retrieve and write release-level relationships (e.g.: URLs, "
"composer, lyricist, performer, conductor, or DJ mixer) to your files. You "
"must have this enabled to use Picard to retrieve cover art."
msgstr ""

#: ../../config/options_metadata.rst:41
msgid "**Use track relationships**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../config/options_metadata.rst:43
msgid ""
"Check to write track-level relationships (e.g.: composer, lyricist, "
"performer, or remixer) to your files."
msgstr ""

#: ../../config/options_metadata.rst:45
msgid "**Guess track number and title from filename if empty**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../config/options_metadata.rst:47
msgid ""
"If checked, Picard will try to guess a file's track number or title from the "
"filename if the ``tracknumber`` or ``title`` tag is empty."
msgstr ""

#: ../../config/options_metadata.rst:49
msgid "**Translate names when available**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../config/options_metadata.rst:51
msgid ""
"Picard can be set to provide translations of some items based on the "
"available information in the MusicBrainz database. The items that can be "
"translated are:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../config/options_metadata.rst:53
msgid "Artist names"
msgstr ""

#: ../../config/options_metadata.rst:54
msgid "Album titles"
msgstr ""

#: ../../config/options_metadata.rst:55
msgid "Track titles"
msgstr ""

#: ../../config/options_metadata.rst:57
msgid ""
"When checked, Picard will check each of the selected locales in order to see "
"whether an item has an alias for that locale. If it does, Picard will use "
"that alias instead of the item name when tagging. For example, if you have "
"selected locales of \"English (Canadian)\" and \"English (US)\", and there "
"are aliases for \"English (US)\", \"English\" and \"Greek\", then the "
"\"English (US)\" alias will be used."
msgstr ""

#: ../../config/options_metadata.rst:59
msgid ""
"Note that Picard will attempt to use the first exact match first. For "
"example, if you have selected locales of \"English (Canadian)\", \"English "
"(US)\" and \"Greek, and there are aliases for \"English\" and \"Greek\", "
"then the \"Greek\" alias will be used."
msgstr ""

#: ../../config/options_metadata.rst:61
msgid ""
"If there are no exact matches to any of the selected locales, then Picard "
"will attempt to find a match based on the root locale. For example, if you "
"have selected locales of \"English (Canadian)\", \"English (US)\" and "
"\"Greek (Cyprus)\", and there are aliases for \"English (UK)\" and "
"\"Greek\", then the \"English (UK)\" alias will be used."
msgstr ""

#: ../../config/options_metadata.rst:63
msgid ""
"If there is no match for the selected locale for an artist and \"English\" "
"is the selected locale, Picard can optionally use the artist sort name "
"(which is, by Style Guideline, stored in Latin script) as a fallback. This "
"is enabled by checking the \"Use artist sort name for translation\" option."
msgstr ""

#: ../../config/options_metadata.rst:65
msgid "**Preferred locales**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../config/options_metadata.rst:67
msgid ""
"To select which locales to use, click the :guilabel:`Select...` button "
"beside the list of selected locales. This will bring up a new dialog window "
"where you can add, remove or reorder your list of selected locales."
msgstr ""

#: ../../config/options_metadata.rst:80 ../../config/options_metadata.rst:103
msgid ""
"Once you are satisfied with your selections, click the :guilabel:`Save` "
"button to transfer the list to your option settings and close the dialog. "
"Note that the changes will not be saved permanently until you click the :"
"guilabel:`Make It So!` button."
msgstr ""

#: ../../config/options_metadata.rst:82
msgid "**Ignore name translation for these language scripts**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../config/options_metadata.rst:84
msgid ""
"Sometimes you may not want to have the items translated if they appear in a "
"certain character set script. When checked, this option will tell Picard to "
"not perform the translation if it is written using one of the selected "
"scripts."
msgstr ""

#: ../../config/options_metadata.rst:86
msgid ""
"Each selected script includes a matching threshold value used to determine "
"if that script should be used. When a name is evaluated to determine if it "
"matches one of your selected scripts, it is first parsed to determine which "
"scripts are represented in the name, and what weighted percentage of the "
"name belongs to each script. Then each of your selected scripts are checked, "
"and if the name contains characters belonging to the script and the "
"percentage of script characters in the name meets or exceeds the match "
"threshold specified for the script, then the name will not be translated."
msgstr ""

#: ../../config/options_metadata.rst:88
msgid ""
"For example, if \"Artist names\" is enabled with the locale set to "
"\"English\", and you enable \"Ignore name translation for these language "
"scripts\" with the scripts set to \"Greek (30%)\" and \"Cyrillic (50%)\", "
"any artist names that contain 30% Greek characters or 50% Cyrillic "
"characters will not be translated and will appear in their origin form."
msgstr ""

#: ../../config/options_metadata.rst:90
msgid ""
"To select which character set scripts to use and their weighting thresholds, "
"click the :guilabel:`Select...` button beside the list of selected scripts. "
"This will bring up a new dialog window where you can add, edit or remove "
"items in your list of selected scripts."
msgstr ""

#: ../../config/options_metadata.rst:105
msgid "**Use artist sort name for translation**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../config/options_metadata.rst:107
msgid ""
"When this option is enabled, if there is no match for the selected locale "
"for an artist, Picard can use the artist sort name (which is, by Style "
"Guideline, stored in Latin script) as a fallback."
msgstr ""

#: ../../config/options_metadata.rst:109
msgid "**Various artists**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../config/options_metadata.rst:111
msgid "Choose how you want the \"Various Artists\" artist spelled."
msgstr ""

#: ../../config/options_metadata.rst:113
msgid "**Standalone recordings**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../config/options_metadata.rst:115
msgid "Choose how you want \"Standalone recordings\" to be grouped."
msgstr ""

#: ../../config/options_metadata.rst:121
msgid ""
"Details: :doc:`options_releases` / :doc:`options_genres` / :doc:"
"`options_ratings`"
msgstr ""
